-- Harbhajan Singh's Century Helps India to Draw 1st Test Against New Zealand
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2010-11-08T10:53:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/harbhajan-singh-s-century-helps-india-to-draw-1st-test-against-new-zealand.html
Spin bowler  Harbhajan Singh  scored
his first century and VVS Laxman made 91 as India recovered to
draw the first cricket Test against New Zealand.  Harbhajan, caught by BJ Watling off Ross Taylor for 115,
and Laxman put on 163 for the seventh wicket. The hosts had
slumped to 15-5 and 65-6, facing likely defeat at Ahmedabad.  Top-ranked India totaled 266 in its second innings after
making 487 in its first. New Zealand, which hasn’t won a series
in India in eight attempts, made 459 and 22-1. Chris Martin took
5-63 in India’s second innings.  The second match in a three-Test series starts at Hyderabad
on Nov. 12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Peter-Joseph Hegarty  in London at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 